Fabulous food....
Very good. Staff was nice too

Randomly came across this restaurant on our brief stopover in Oahu. The service was excellent but the food was exceptional with fresh ingredients and well prepared. Recommend this place very highly if you are looking for good Italian food with a nice ambiance
Fantastic :)
Tasty and tasty

Called them and was told we could just show up and be seated in 5 minutes as there were lots of cancellations.  when we arrived we were told it was going to be a one hour wait!   Asked if we wanted to wait,  I said no thx and they just turned their back to me  and walked away.  Terrible customer service.

We made a reservation and treated so disrespectful by the entire staff. No pizza. No steak. No service.  Don't come here. You make a reservation and wait for over 45 minutes, then after an hour your food doesn't come, no water refills and the rudest waitress staff I've ever encountered. Check my reviews. DON'T COME HERE!!!
Best service snd best Italian food in Hawaii!!!
Lovely atmosphere and delicious food
The pasta and desserts were amazing! This is a real gem

Mediterraneo exceeded my expectations.  Had the Tako Salad and Caprese as appetizers, and Mare Nero as my entrée. Everything was delicious. Great customer service. I will be coming back to try out the rest of the menu and for more Tako Salad.
Best piccata I've had in awhile
Great atmosphere food is splendid and scrumptious! Will come again to eat pasta! 😋
The food is always amazing, but more importantly, Fabrizio (the owner) is the life of the party and the servers are the best.

The pasta and rissoto were excellent! The appetizers and salads were overpriced and clearly sized to share. I would propose half-sized options be placed on the menu. The Italian proprietor was eccentric and flagrantly did not wear a mask during the COVID pandemic as he walked throughout the restaurant. They don't have a full bar.
The food is delicious and service was so friendly and portions are huge!

I've been here multiple times now and can officially say that it's legitimate Italian food. As someone who's from the NYC area, my bar for Italian food is set very high, and this place exceeds my expectations. I've now had their red sauce and Marsala, and they were both excellent. Their seafood is delicious, the chicken was cooked perfectly, the pasta is absolutely on point, and Fabrizio’s house-made sausage is stellar. On top of that, Fabrizio makes sure all his guests are happy, and his staff, including Kyle, are great. Highly recommend.

Friendly. Good dinner. Amazing dessert! I bake a lot and they had a very creative creme brulet cheese cake. They have a very isolated out door table to the left of the entrance. My first sit down dinner since covid. Used the hawaii resturant card.
This place took me back to my time in Naples, Italy. The chef is amazing.  The staff is lovely and attentive. I recommend this place if you'd like a taste of Italy. The bolognese was spot on.
eh, maybe don't order the pizza. the other dishes were good. expect to spend time dining.
Love the atmosphere here - tiny & cozy with a nice outdoor patio area. Food is great & reasonably priced (plus they provide some amazing flatbread to whet your appetite). Free parking in the back.

Every time we're there, we are served wonderful, authentic italian food.  The owner is eccentric but nice, and passionate about serving his customers good food.  His family helps and they are all friendly.  Go here for a great experience. 🤓.
Always delicious and great atmosphere. Been coming here for years and hopefully will for many more!  Please help support them during covid-19 so we don't lose another great local business. 🙏 🙏 🙏

I expected that Squid ink pasta has Squid ink sauce, but it was ink pasta and goat cheese sauce. I tastes very delicious but smells gamy. I'm okay with that, but my family didn't like the gamy smelt. It's slightly pricy. I'd like to try Squid ink risotto next time. The owner is very funny and happy guy. The restaurant itself is very cozy and pretty and cute. the workers are friendly too.

Great dinner at an unassuming place.  The mozzarella in the caprese is the best I have ever had.  My wife had the fruiti di mare and loved it.  I had the carbonara and it was excellent...plenty of big chunks of delicious bacon.  Street parking was no big deal.  Best Italian food we have had in the year we have lived here. We will be back.
The food was amazing and the owner and his wife are funny and great hosts. I can't wait to go back.
Love love love this restaurant. Food. Ambiance. Service. All excellent!
Delicious, friendly, such a nice place to eat

One of the best dining experiences, I've ever experienced.  I haven't had any good Italian food on the island untill I ate here!  They serve complimentary fresh baked bread with olive oil and balsamic vinegar  I'm not a big tomato fan, but the Bruschetta was a delicious and refreshing appetizer.  The Lobster Ravioli is a must try. It's perfectly balanced with fresh lobster and creamy white sauce.  I had the Hazelnut Ice cream for dessert and it's basically the best gelato I've ever had. Think about Nutella Icecream!  The owner Fabrizio, originally from Roma, and is one of the nicest people I've met on the island, very personable. He even escorted us out!  I highly recommend this place, and will definitely be back!  Mahalos, Fabrizio and staff for the amazing experience!  Photo credit goes to Paul Millar
Dry pasta and gave me spoon to eat

Quaint little outdoor seating area, extensive menu. The pasta was perfectly salted and al dente, we ordered STRANGOLAPRETI  The homemade sausage was to die for along with the pappardelle. It was really beautiful.

This place is so good, the owner/chef/ godfather does an amazing job with his culinary creation from his seafood rissoto to his amazing mushroom truffle pizza and probably the best Tiramisu I have ever had, but don't take my word for it give it a try and you will be hooked this little place is one of the best kept secrets in town.
Always a great meal
What a marvelous experience! Good was superb. Staff were helpfully attentive. Whole feel of restaurant was friendly and happy. Definitely look forward to visiting again.
(Translated by Google) To good taste!  (Original) Al buon gusto!

Bellisimo! I've known the owner Fabrizio since he was a partner at the cutest wine bar called Pane Vino in Waikiki. I LOVED going there. Mediterraneo is an authentic Italian restaurant in Honolulu - amazing pizza is cooked in the traditional oven outside on the lanai and he visits each table usually making guests drink a Grapa or Limoncello shot with him. He just opened a place next door for intimate events as well.

This place is amazing. The Chef is Italian, the waitress was Italian and the owner was Italian. How much more can you ask for from an Italian Restaurant. The Mexican guy cooking the woodfired oven pizza was amazing also, I believe his name was Alberto. Can't wait to go back!

(Translated by Google) The location was easy to understand, there was a pizza oven outside the store, and the staff welcomed me. Alcohol is also sold in the store, and 10% off for cash. The food was all delicious without waiting too much.  (Original) 場所も分かりやすく、店の外にピザ焼き釜が有って、スタッフさんも気持ちよく迎えて下さいました。店内でお酒も売ってるし、キャッシュなら10%OFF。 料理はさほど待たずに全て美味しかったです。

My husband and I stumbled on this little place when another Italian place didn’t serve wine. So very glad!  The food is authentic and amazing and honestly we don’t mind the price. Service can be slow, but we don’t care. We never feel rushed. Everyone is friendly. It’s little and quaint but the food is on point. You must try the creme brûlée cheesecake.
Very good food. Very pricey. Watch for the 20% tip added for groups of 6. Very friendly staff.
Yum. Some wait but worth it.

Homey delicious Italian food. Not suuuuper authentic, but it was delicious. Surprisingly the lasagna is the way to go. Huge portion with a decent layer of meat among sauce and noodle. A perfect mess.  The squid ink pasta was okay. Honestly there was too much cheese in the sauce, so it was a bit coying.  Service was inconsistent but unintentional I think. For example, our dishes all came out at a different time. It's a small kitchen so I don't blame them too much for that.

Very good food. Had a special; Stewed Oxtail osso buco style with saffron rizoto. shared pizza as appetizer. Will definitley go back. nice outdoor seating area near the wood burning pizza oven. Service could have been better.
Authentic Italian food. A bit on the pricey side. Chef/Owner is from Rome.
Really good food and great wine selection!
(Translated by Google) It was really delicious  (Original) 凄く美味しいかった
Very good and authentic, the owner himself even offered up a great choice of wine which I throughly enjoyed

This place was great! The owner and the servers were very nice and friendly.  The food was great! All i can say is FRESH HOUSE MADE PASTA!!!!!! There is a huge difference between boxed/dried pasta and freshly made pasta. I would definitely recommend this place.  (The house made meatballs were pretty darn yummy too!)

(Translated by Google) Very rich everything and the pleasant atmosphere, but the dishes are very small .. the rest impeccable!  (Original) Muy rico todo y el ambiente agradable, pero los platos son muy pequeños.. el resto impecable ¡¡¡¡

It has been a long time since I just wanted to leave a place to go somewhere else. I truly was excited to try this place but everything was lackluster, other than the bread you are provided when you sit down but even that and waters took 10+ mins. Chicken Picatta seemed a bit rubbery and since it was all cut up not sure if it was a fresh breast, first time ever that I've seen served like that and wife's meal was just ok, but then ok is a frozen italian dinner. The place seems run down rather than homey, well we learned not to trust previous reviews so much, gentleman that served us barely checked on us and took almost 30 mins to pay once the bill was at the table. Very disappointed

(Translated by Google) I saw the word of mouth and made a reservation and visited with my family Was it crowded Waiting outside and forgetting ... The store clerk in the outside area also feels bad I didn't know if I was busy with my family, but it wasn't a word of mouth. The owner seems to change the store When I told Chubby, it was a terrible response. I wonder why there are shops that get this when they get busy. We waited, but went to kind minato. This is where I go for great Italian food. The pizza is how I like fresh ingredients, thin crust brick oven. I recently tried the Tako salad, the octopus is twice cooked... So tender I could cut with my fork. Bring your one bottle!
Absolutely fantastic! Everyone is so nice and the food was amazing!!! Found this place on chance and everything and everyone is so welcoming! Definitely a an “off the beaten path” gem!
Cozy romantic restaurant with authentic Italian cuisine. Get the espresso after cena. Still haven't tried the pizza but it looked good.

I am really not sure if its always like this, or we came on an off night but we didn't have a very good experience. We were seated outside and given waters. Then after about 30 min or so, I had to go inside and ask for service because no one came back. They came out took our order, food came at a decent time but then that was it. My husband had to go in again and asked for a check when we were long done after our meals. Not once someone just came out to check on us. The table next to us had the same experience. Food was okay. Paid $24 for a chicken dish and had to add $4 for a little bit of pasta. Wasnt anything special. Husband had fettuccini that was sprinkled with lobster. We were pretty disappointed overall.

Wow an exciting experience.   Fabrizio, the owner & his partner are hospitable, gregarious & generous.   Absolutely one of the most enjoyable dining experiences my wife & I have had while on vacation. I highly recommend it.  You will enjoy it.

Characterful head staff. Warm busy Tuscany-colored interior. Enjoyed excellent burratta with EVO ripe local 🍅 and basil, 🐙 salad, gnocchi with hearty Gorgonzola, parpadelle with porcini, elegant tiramisu. Adjacent wine shop/closet to buy curated bottles, $20 corkage. Parking is hit or miss, with a small lot to the makai side of the restaurant. Limited availability of reservations. Overall a true 👍

Great place, I have been a long time customer. And always recommend this place to friends. The food is amazing, and the owner is so friendly and is always hanging out in the dining area making sure everyone is happy. I also really love their new location because it has great outdoor seating as well.

NEVER judge a book by its cover. Food was amazing and could easily be served in any upscale restaurant in a major metropolitan area. They have been around for 30 years and we love that they want to stay small, casual and intimate. Italian food made by Italian cooks. What more could you ask for? We would come back to Hawaii just to eat here.

Great atmosphere, great food, superb staff. The owner walked around and not only greeted the guests but also took the time to chat. Everyone was incredibly passionate about the food and the experience. Hands down one of the best restaurants in Hawaii.

(Translated by Google) There is a distance from the city, but the store that authentic Italian has the taste you ❗️ small in Waikiki baked in a stone oven are filled with lively and delicious smell ♪  (Original) 街中からは距離がありますが石窯で焼き上げた本格イタリアンがワイキキで味わえます❗️ こじんまりとした店内は賑やかで美味しい匂いで充満してます♪
Good food. But make sure to make reservation. It gets crowded.
(Translated by Google) The clerk was nice and friendly. The garden was lively.  (Original) 店員さんも気さくで良かったです。ガーデンも賑やかでした。
This place is unlike a lot of Italian restaurants. The food was decent and there were a lot of people. Parking can be an issue, otherwise, it was a good experience.
Food was great but service was slow. They need more workers.

Food was awesome. Atmosphere is very homey inside. Carbanara is my favorite and they do justice to the dish. Lasagna was cheesy, flavorful and fresh pasta. Triamisu was a great finish to the meal. Not overly sweet and light.
Excellent pasta. Owner was very personable. Don't forget your dessert!
Very good personal and delicious foods.
Incredible!  Great atmosphere
Food is always good here.  This is the original place to get pasta. The owner is so passionate in what he does. He comes around and greets others. Its quiet  nice.
Great food and service.  A gem.

There are plenty of squid, shrimp, shellfish and fish, and the taste is steeped in, so it's really delicious. And the pasta of Aragosta (lobster) is also great. You can choose your favorite noodles for pasta. You can choose your favorite bottle of wine from the wine space at the back of the store. It may be advantageous than glass wine. The atmosphere of the shop is calming down like a home. The shop closes relatively early, and a bit unfriendly waitress is sometimes a scratch, but it is tempting to eat the excellent Italian food that chefs from Naples create. Wonderful ambiance and exquisite food and wine. I will say the service was what really did it for me though. Apparently I was taken care of by the chef... an exquisitely attractive and kind Italian. Woof. If you’re lucky like me you’ll get a side of eye candy with your antipasti. Talk Italian to me any day...
Outstanding food and host. Homemade, authentic, fresh, wholesome food made with simple ingredients and prepared with equal parts love and passion. Best Italian in Hawaii.
Amazing food.  Fabrizio is such a great guy. Great atmosphere!
Great atmosphere.
Great atmosphere with great service.
Lasagna was Excellent.

An amazing spot away from all the crowds.   They are vegetarian friendly and their customer service is above one's own expectations.  I highly recommend their dinner time.  They know how to make a romantic setting.
Comfort Italian food.
Awesome place, great Italian food. Super nice staff, very clean, quick service too. Arguably the best Italian food on the island.
Authentic ITALIAN food...every dish was delicious! Great energy and ambience! Best in HAWAII...by far!!
The best Italian restaurant by far! Excellent service 👌
Very small seating space, we had to beg for service, it took more than an hour to get pasta, and finally very small portions
Lovely little place, great service and wonderful pasta.

Food is very good but not excellent. There are some issues with service. When you enter the restaurant you are not greeted and you don't know where to go or whom to talk to.  It is a bit chaotic when they are busy.  I am giving them 5 stars because they give you 10% discount if you pay cash instead of credit card.
Food was DELICIOUS  and enjoyed the Italian language spoken by the  staff made me feel like eating at a real Italian restaurant. Mahalo Mediterraneo
Not bad not the best but still good. Quirky owner . A but unorganized
Food is amazing!
Very real original Italian food. Highly recommend.

Food is really good. Great authentic Italian cuisine and beer selection.  Also have Italian wines and desserts. They use fresh pasta and pizzas to order in their outdoor brick oven. I ordered a steak which they unfortunately forgot to fire and I had to take it home. However, it may have been one of the best steaks I've eaten at a restaurant. I've eaten steaks at many of the finest steakhouses around but this was on par with all. If not slightly better at the price.
The night started out rough with below average service but the food was AMAZING!!!!! The environment was awesome also.
Best Italian I've had on Oahu
Food is so ono and I would give 5 star but parking is a struggle at times.  Cute place and owner is a cool guy.
Best Italian restaurant I have been to since returning from Europe.
The Ambiance, food and service was absolutely awesome.   And, it was worthy of the price....   The best I've had since my last trip to Italy.

(Translated by Google) The food was delicious, but at the time of checkout, my sister, who had a lot of miniskirt tattoos, was given a slip with 20% tip added. You can choose a percentage of the tip yourself, and this is the first time that you have filled it out and handed a slip. I can't speak English very well, so I guess I was licked. The service is not good, there is no drink menu and there are few wine choices. When I said that it was strange that the tip was filled in without permission, I said that I made excuses, but I felt the worst. On the last night in Hawaii, I took the trouble to walk I took my child with me and it made me feel terrible. Please be aware that Japanese people are more likely to get bogged down depending on their English proficiency. The food tastes like Tabelog 3 in Japan. The glass of wine was too sweet and didn't taste good. I love this place. MEOW is so friendly and the best hostess ever. Her husband is amazing too. And they provide the best atmosphere for amazing Italian cuisine. I highly recommend eating here for the food and entertainment.

LOVE. Seriously, I moved recently from Staten Island NY and I have been dying for Italian food like home, Sunday dinner style- and this was the best I have tried!! (And I’ve been a lotttt of places here). Absolutely amazing, you won’t regret going- great prices amazing food. And it’s not salty, it’s literally perfect!
Food is amazing and they have a small room where you can buy your wines and beers. The place is so authentic the servers have Italian accents and the chef even come out to check on you!

Wonderful Italian food and service!  We've lived in the neighborhood for 9 years and it was our first visit.  I don't understand why it has taken us so long!  Definitely will be back, our favorite Italian place to go to!!

This place is the real deal!!! So yum. I used to live in Italy and hands down authentic home made Italiano food. I’ve never been to a better place in the U.S. for italiano cuisine. Seriously!! A must go if you want real Italian food from Roma, Italy!!!
Great food and excellent people.
We just moved here from Italy and this place was so good it made use home sick. If you want great Italian and great people go there as soon as you can.
Wonderful authentic Italian food. BYOB or purchase wine from their in house store.  Love this place.  It is small so reservations are recommended. There is also outdoor seating.
Casual dining. Good selection of wine to enjoy.
Our favorite Italian on the Hawaiian islands. Period. Delicious food and wine. And the atmosphere is festive and warm. Go here now.
Fabrizio & staff make you feel at home. The food is always fresh, good & consistent. We asked him to select a wine with our choices,  it's perfect. This is the place to bring your family & friends.
Food is very tasty.  The parking is a bit limited.  You get 10% discount if you pay with cash.
Loved the food and ambiance! Super cozy! Would go back again!

We shared dishes family style and everything was very good. No false steps. It does get busy, and they don't take reservations! The veal piccata was particularly tasty, with loads of capers, the way life was meant to be!!! Yes, you can bring wine. Edit: It appears they DO take reservations, at least sometimes. It gets CROWDED!
Delicious authentic food, you MUST try the tiramisu it’s amazing!

Even if we thought the blonde hostess(?) looked a little unorganized and word her skirt too short. (suggestion: use pantyhose if you must bend over to serve) Our male server Kyle(?) was super friendly and took care of us even when we started off with the woman serving us. And the food and red wine was excellent in this very quaint establishment.
Food was very good, nice atmosphere    And would recommend for a casual evening.
Loved the tako ( octopus salad) actually loved everything.. waitstaff, owner and cook were very nice too.
Great food and prices, service is good
Couldn't be happier with the service and quality of cuisine.

Excellent food, informal atmosphere, reasonable prices.  The portions are sufficiently large that it is not recommended to do the traditional, antipasto, the pasta, the secondo (or meat), and the dolce.  There is a reasonable selection of appetizer offerings, but I think a better course would be to jump first into the pasta and then the secondo.  There was a two-pound prime rib steak special the most recent time we went, which was good for sharing.  Desserts were good.  You may bring your own wines.
The BEST Italian cuisine around. A lovely intimate and small setting makes for a perfect meal.
Most items are delicious depending on what you like. Very good atmosphere, parking is very tight and limited so go early
Delicious food, great homely atmosphere, amazingly friendly and did I say the food was amazing? This is special and the owner is a classic! Go for the food, go for the service, just go!!!
10/10 will return. Bummed I didn't take any pics or videos. But will do on my next visit.
Fantastic food and atmosphere!

Delicious Italian Food great service. A must place to eat...

What a hidden gem. Off the beaten path, away from the hustle and bustle. The owner has so much charm and charisma and I hear his recipes are all his mother's original Italian recipes! The Ravioli Aragosta (lobster) is to die for!!!!
Amazing place, spectacular food, a restaurant run with love.    What a find that made our trip that much more special.
This was a fantastic meal. My wife and I are here tonight (July 26th 2017) for our anniversary. It feels as if you are eating with family. The food is phenomenal. We will be returning again, soon.
The best puttanesca pasta and seafood saffron risotto and tiramisu ... it was a treat to have dinner here ... the owner Fabricio was so nice with us !!
The Owner is a crazy passionate guy...you will love it!
Been here several times everything on the menu has been delicious service and staff is wonderful highly recommended
Owner is very warm and friendly. Food is great Italian. Not super expensive. Homey and cozy inside.
The food is delicious and the staff is so friendly and welcoming! Perfect place to bring a bottle of wine and enjoy yourself with a group of friends!

Cozy feeling even though we sat outside. Owner came to greet each and every table (I like that).  Food tastes ok, a little salty for me (I had spinach ravioli. Ravioli is great but the sauce is a little too salty). One little detail that needs improvement is the waiter. Needs a little lighter hand when set plates on table. I felt like he slammed the plates in front of us. Really like the owner. He takes time to make sure we are happy. Not many place does that anymore. 5 stars for the owner 😊

This place is super cute, the food is spectacular, but the best part is the owner/chef! He invites you in and makes you feel right at home, you feel like his friend even though you just met him. Had the mushroom ravioli and bruschetta and it was spectacular, will definitely be back!
been here over 10 times.  love it!  always same cook dishing out same great tasty food each time!!! best Italian in Hawaii!!
Super delicious food!
Very original Italian food. Been here several times love it. Recommend this place👍
(Translated by Google) Recommended in a homely atmosphere with a good balance of taste and price. I hope the menu is a little more rich.  (Original) 味も値段もバランスよく家庭的な店の雰囲気でお勧め。 もう少しメニュー豊富ならいいんだけどな。
